CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1952, pg. 27, reads: "Ready for Comeback - Bob Baker, center, signs a contract for his coming fight here Oct. 28. The bout will be Baker's first in almost a year.  The promising battler has been sidelined with injured hands.  Others in photo are standing left, to right, T. W. Stephens, Wilkinsburg burgess; Promoter Anthony (Cowboy) DeLuca.  Seated next to Baker is his manager, William Better. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: William Bettor, T. W. Stephen, and Anthony "Cowboy" DeLuca, surrounding boxer Bob Baker signing contract, in office
